<br>
(*waves to Jz* Heh, yeah, I got the Diablo II bug out of my system and am back in Norrath again, to answer your question in a previous post.  :-)  )<br>
<br>
Well, while I was reading your latest meeting log, and the ideas about events being bantered about, one popped into my mind that you all might find enjoyable...Well, it's more of an abstract idea, and I am sure you could expand on it.<br>
<br>
It would be a Good vs. Evil Starving Newbie race, and here is how it would work...<br>
<br>
Both teams would each comprise 1 group of up to 6 people.  The 6th person, (or 3rd person, if you decide to do it with only 3, etc.) would be a totally naked level 1 newbie who is starving and dying of thirst, which would cause him/her to not regen HP or mana (reason for that below)<br>
<br>
The goal for the Good team...Your Starving newbie would be a Dark Elf Necro, and you must use whatever means necessary to escort him or her safely to the very top of the Hall of Truth in Freeport, where a representative from another guild's Evil team would then hand you an item, and then must be escorted safely back to the starting point.  The team with the fastest time would win.<br>
<br>
The goal for the Evil team...Your Starving newbie would be a Half-Elf Paladin, and you must use whatever means necessary to escort him or her safely to the very top of the Hall of the Dead in Neriak's Third Gate, where a representative from another guild's Good team would then hand you an item, and then must be escorted safely back to the starting point.  The team with the fastest time would win.<br>
<br>
Each guild would have a Good and Evil team<br>
<br>
The 2 guilds who have the best average time for both teams would be declared the winners of the race, 1st and 2nd place.  If a Starving newbie dies twice, that guild is disqualified.<br>
<br>
<br>
Good team starting point would be the Freeport dock.<br>
<br>
Evil team starting point would be just inside Neriak, at the Nektulos zone border.  <br>
<br>
This assures there are 4 zonings for each team, and each team has a safe starting point.<br>
<br>
The top 2 guilds after the race then enter the final elimination round, where both guilds group their good and evil newbies together, and the opposing guilds' teams have a fist fight to the finish.  No spells, no armor, no buffs during the fist fight, just a true Starving Newbie beatdown, hehe.  So before you put all those points into Stamina for extra health, perhaps into STR for extra beatdown power?  Remember, you are starving/thirsty, so you won't have any regen at all.  Running around evasively and sitting to try to regen that extra 5 or 6 HP during the fight won't work.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
The guild with the last team standing is the winner of the event.<br>
<br>
Well, that's the idea, I guess. <br>
<br>
I am sure you could think of ways to improve upon that.<br>
<br>
Oh, and don't look to me to organize something like this.  I am not good at that sort of thing. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Ciao!<br>
<br>
